[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying class structure**\n\nI need to determine if the JCERSAPrivateKey implements Serializable. Since RSAPrivateKey extends PrivateKey and Serializable, it does. I should create a subclass with a serialVersion. \n\nNow, should I use a static inner class for TestRsaPrivateKey? The rule about not using \"$\" in test file names is puzzling. Maybe it’s best to avoid generating it altogether. I could create a non-public top-level class instead since top-level test classes should be public. A nested private static helper seems like a solid option too!\n\n**Understanding serialization rules**\n\nThe rule states that I shouldn't use \"$\" in test class or file names, but that's regarding generated files, not necessarily true for my situation. \n\nNow, if I'm serializing a subclass, it will invoke Serializable behavior. This is because if the subclass is Serializable and the superclass, JCERSAPrivateKey, has a private writeObject method, it can only be invoked for each Serializable class. Wait, does Java serialization really call the private writeObject for each Serializable class? It seems like that could change how I approach this serialization task!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00da38914ad6f671016a25e74a2d4c819486abfa6999d718c2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJedf-XjAUEWifBqeVctZG68yWd8fiiAP-fk8G-mX1nNwYzXqLrqRjTjvCPNzbyzWgDz4EHNIdYVc932FOopm98VLxaQIyIRs5a2KRPpiQpqZ9_WNXSatkOTCPgEIFfDfmK6fe-GqQrjWhh45BnZAFZHPhWvpIm4WdPRK0O1eW6fI96A1ZohU29BO7FJFNCWcHoZUcHmcQla337XYjBykYvzwqtH-UdZthmMLRvfWOvbEL4EywsBA4iSLhtekZXWnIj_4-kKxgT5GXPznDHM2Z3uQyskNCm2yX6bZF3GynoLds0XRnDaeW1Lq8t-Pj7Rd02lK91rxCvouvqriTWssPvU9m8DkHBomNk2X0RhMZvNJuYi9dTkl3RiS5NpvcNtvpsua0LL26VEBQxBssMLAr9UZMP1qUMZISay-zR688FPcV0t6-r4FgEt2Gza8uDs-DwKwEAMKwsRbrdRwmf67SA5nGJnKJHB4NculOz7cHvl5y9FhhCNkbSr-rqwRS26qQqQmGCp-HEXlgNY_ACNlfO08BA7Qor3UCVeYoViboidjJFlBeDCE